Meet Paige, our citizen of the week!<br><br>Paige lives at <a href='/home/?user=paiger007'>10060 Broken Tree Bend</a> in one of Westridge's most fashionable, spacious houses.  Paige has been enjoying life in her new home (which she shares with her many pets) since August 19, 2005.<br><br>Though Paige has lived in Millsberry for less than a year, you'd never know it by the large group of friends she has!  Paige is very outgoing, so she can easily strike up a conversation with just about anyone.  When she first moved to Millsberry, Paige tried out for the soccer team, and by the end of her first practice, she had practically made friends with the entire team!  In addition to having an outgoing personality, Paige is quite charming, which helps her draw even the shyest person out of their shell.  When you add Paige's sparkling wit to her friendliness and charm, it's plain to see why she is an ideal conversationalist!<br><br>Paige isn't always a social butterfly, though.  When she wants some quiet time to herself, she'll often turn on one of her punk, country, or modern rock CDs and indulge in her other favorite pastime - drawing.  Paige's drawings can be bright and peppy, like her pink and orange creations, or moody and deep, like her charcoal-black drawings.  Her artistic talent really is as diverse as her musical taste!<br><br>When she isn't busy minding the net at a soccer game or sketching her latest masterpiece, Paige likes hanging out at her best friend's house.  Sometimes, if the weather is warm, they'll head over to <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/peabody_park">Peabody Park</a> to do some soccer drills or just sit in the shade and talk.  During the winter, or when it's too wet to play outside, Paige and her friends usually visit the <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/complex/theater.phtml">movie theater</a> at the <a href="http://www.millsberry.com/complex">Downtown Entertainment Complex</a> to catch the latest film releases.<br><br>Thanks for being a fine citizen, Paige, and congratulations on being named Millsberry's citizen of the week!</div>
